`setFocusable()` is actually a method from the `Component` class in Swing.

    public void setFocusable(boolean focusable)

It lets the component (in your case, `JPanel` which *extends* `Component`) have the power of getting focused. It doesn&#39;t actually set the component to be focused, it just indicates if the component can be focused or not, which is determined by the boolean parameter passed.

