Here is what you need :

**First add this dependency to dependencies :**

	com.andrognito.patternlockview:patternlockview:1.0.0

**Then add PatternLockView to your XML file :**

	&lt;com.andrognito.patternlockview.PatternLockView
		android:id=&quot;@+id/mypatternlockview&quot;
		android:layout_width=&quot;match_parent&quot;
		android:layout_height=&quot;wrap_content&quot;
		android:padding=&quot;8dp&quot;/&gt;

**Then import these to your pattern activity :**

	import com.andrognito.patternlockview.PatternLockView;
	import com.andrognito.patternlockview.utils.*;
	import com.andrognito.patternlockview.listener.*;

**Then add the PatternLockView :**

	private PatternLockView mypatternlockview;

**Then add this to the onCreate void :**

	mypatternlockview = (PatternLockView) findViewById(R.id.mypatternlockview);
	mypatternlockview.addPatternLockListener(new PatternLockViewListener() {
			@Override
			public void onStarted() {
				
			}
			
			@Override
			public void onProgress(List&lt;PatternLockView.Dot&gt; _pattern) {
				
			}
			
			@Override
			public void onComplete(List&lt;PatternLockView.Dot&gt; _pattern) {
				if (PatternLockUtils.patternToString(mypatternlockview, _pattern).equals(savedPattern)) {
					//The pattern is correct, you can pass
					mypatternlockview.setViewMode(PatternLockView.PatternViewMode.CORRECT);
					//Launch the app
				}
				else {
					//The pattern is incorrect, you can&#39;t pass
					mypatternlockview.setViewMode(PatternLockView.PatternViewMode.WRONG);
					mypatternlockview.clearPattern();
				}
			}
			
			@Override
			public void onCleared() {
				
			}
		});
	}

```savedPattern``` is a ```String``` that stores the saved pattern

When the user completes drawing the pattern the application checks if the enterd pattern matches the saved pattern

you can save a pattern using another PatternLockView in another activity &amp; SharedPreferences, if you want to know how to do that just ask me in the chat

