To answer your question, no I don&#39;t think there is.

However, it strikes me that what you are doing is equivalent to this:

    NetSession makeProxy(NetSession session) {
        session.connect();
        if (session instanceof HttpSession) {
            HttpSession httpSession = (HttpSession) session;
            httpSession.useRestApi();

            // do something else
        } else {
            return session;
        }
    }

In short, your complicated Guava code doesn&#39;t achieve anything that you can&#39;t do *more elegantly* using `instanceof`.

You don&#39;t need to use reflection to find an interface if you then just intend to use the interface non-reflectively.

